io.s4.zeno
Class PartMap

java.lang.Object
  io.s4.zeno.PartMap

public class PartMap
extends java.lang.Object

A mapping from Part ids to Parts. Functionality is provided for: 1. acquiring a set of parts based on the job spec 2. acquiring a set of parts based on a specified desired count 3. identifying a collection of parts that consume a specified amount of resources 4. adding to and removing from the mapping 5. Looking up Parts corresponding to Ids

getBusy

public java.util.Collection<Part> getBusy(FlexibleResource r)
Get the most busy parts that can fit into a flexible resource constraint. The resource is expanded till some parts are identified to fit into it. Expansion stops when the resource cannot be expanded further.

Parameters:
r - flexible resource constraint into which parts have to be fit.
Returns:
collection of busy parts. Collection is empty if no parts could be fit.

freezeParts

public static boolean freezeParts(java.util.Collection<Part> parts,
                                  long silence,
                                  long timeout)
Freeze a set of parts. Parts are first paused. Then the method waits till no event is sent to any of the parts for a period of time (i.e. the parts are "silent"). If this fails for any part, then the whole operation is rolled back.

When this method returns true, it is guaranteed that all the parts are paused and have been silent for silence milliseconds. If this is not the case, false is returned and the parts are unchanged; some of the parts may have been paused and then resumed.

Parameters:
parts - collection of parts
silence - amount of time for which each part should be silent (milliseconds).
timeout - total time after which the request times out.
Returns:
true, if successful. In particular, false if waiting for silence on any part times out.
